post_text:
The district has a request if we were going to post the number of positive and/or exposed students/staff on our webpage. At this time we are not going to do that since a raw number does not give the entire back story to each individual case. We are going to notify each family of possible exposure or positive cases in their children's classrooms. We will post on Facebook information as it becomes available, but our bottom line is to keep our students safe. We currently have two students in the elementary that are asymptomatic and are at home along with two other students who were exposed. We also have two students at the secondary that are exposed. If there ever a question, please feel free to reach out to me at 641-224-2524.
Dave Harper

8:05 9th Grade
8:10 10th Grade
8:15 11th & 12th Grade

The Jr./Sr. High School will be having a 7th grade orientation on Wednesday, August 19th. Students with a last name between Berg & Parker will arrive @ 6:00 p.m. and those with a last name between Peska & Yates will come @ 7:00 p.m. We made the decision to not hold a 9th grade open house this year, to limit the number of people entering the building. If you have a new student and would like to see our facilities, please don't hesitate to contact me to set up a tour. The first day of school is Monday, August 24th. Please check your emails for updates and guidelines for the new school year. We know this will be a unique school year, but we look forward to serving our Savage families once again! If you have any questions or concerns, please don’t hesitate to contact me.

Shannon Webb
shannon.webb@sigourneyschools.com
(641)622-2010

GAME/BANNER SPONSORS for 2020-21 Season

As part of our Game Sponsorship Program we would like to offer the chance for businesses to display their banners on our football fences. A banner is a great way to showcase your business and help sponsor our programs.

We will be having 3 Home Varsity and 3 JV FB Games this season. With the possibility of hosting a 4th playoff game.

The cost for the season will be 100 dollars and you will provide your own banner. We will also announce our Banner Sponsors throughout the season.

I still have the Banners from last year if any of you are still interested again this year.

Please contact Lee Crawford if you are interested in being a part of this program.

On July 1st our Summer Training will open at school. We are taking every precaution to make we keep our student/athletes safe while training and playing. The following rules will be in place. Please make your student familiar with them:

-No Locker Room Use
-Bring your own Water Bottle full of Water
-Use the bathroom before coming to training
-Closed toe shoes always - NO sandals or Dudes
-Long Sleeves as much as possible
-Wear CLEAN clothes each time you come to train
-Keep a small bottle of hand sanitizer in your car/bag
-Sanitize before you attend training
-Make sure and Social Distance (6 foot)
-Have a mask in your car/bag ready for use
-We will be sanitizing every 30 minutes
-Don't come if you don't feel good or have a temp near 100.3
-Facilities and equipment will be sanitized after use and every 30 minutes
-Students will be educated on remainder of hygiene/distancing routines

Students will also be placed into small PODS to train. Coaches will be setting the PODS and times. Baseball and Softball teams will be in separate PODS until the end of their seasons.
text:

-No Locker Room Use
-Bring your own Water Bottle full of Water
-Use the bathroom before coming to training
-Closed toe shoes always - NO sandals or Dudes
-Long Sleeves as much as possible
-Wear CLEAN clothes each time you come to train
-Keep a small bottle of hand sanitizer in your car/bag
-Sanitize before you attend training
-Make sure and Social Distance (6 foot)
-Have a mask in your car/bag ready for use
-We will be sanitizing every 30 minutes
-Don't come if you don't feel good or have a temp near 100.3
-Facilities and equipment will be sanitized after use and every 30 minutes

post_text:
Popsicles with the Principal

I will be doing a google hangout on Monday at 11:00 with all students in grades 7-12. Please encourage your children to join me. Parents, you are more than welcome to listen in. I emailed each student an invite to the hangout. I will be updating everyone on how the remainder of the school year will look. I will also be discussing Prom & Graduation details. Today has been a difficult for all of us. I miss my kids, my teachers, & everyone within our Savage Family! Stay safe and I hope to see you all on Monday at 11:00

Love you,
Mrs. Webb

For the time being, we would like to go ahead and collect names for our 4 year old preschool program. If you have a child that will turn 4 on or before Sept. 15, 2020, please fill out the link below to get them on the list. Depending the availability of spots, we will also run our prekinder program again for 5 year olds(must be 5 on or before Sept. 15, 2020). post_text: A message from Mrs. Harter!
shared_text:
Jeni Harter is at Sigourney Community School District.
March 27 at 1:03 PM · Sigourney, IA ·

Two weeks now since we have had an in-person JH Science Class. Yes, your JH teachers DO miss you:
your "cringy" TikToks, your groans and moans regarding the 15-minute-free-reading at the beginning of study hall, the spilled slushies, the sound of munching on morning/afternoon snacks. We miss your "ah-ha" moments, the intent you show when that hands-on project is "right up your alley", and the excitement in your step when that 3:30 bell rings. WE MISS YOU!
.
.
.
BTW, make sure to keep plugging away at those Science activities that I sent in Google Classroom! I can't wait to see what some of you come up with ;)
.
.
.
Until then...keep your spirits high, "socialize" the best way you know how through social distancing, and just make this unprecedented time a positive and memorable one!

post_text:
A message from Mr. McCully & Mrs. Clarahan. High school math students, get your creative juices flowing!

Savage High School Math Competition

Due: April 10th
Prize: $25 Casey’s Gift Card
For students in grades 9-12 at Sigourney CSD.

Please submit a video of you and another adult solving a real world Math problem. Be sure to use any algebra or geometry skills in your solution.

The video would be expected to be at least 4 minutes long and would include a collaborative effort among the student and the adult.

A winner will be selected on April 10th. The difficulty of your problem will be considered when selecting a winner, so be sure to challenge yourself.

Submit your videos to:

bronson.mcculley@sigourneyschools.com

Or

donita.clarahan@sigourneyschools.com

post_text: What a great idea! Love our community! SAVAGE STRONG!
shared_text:
Sigourney Fire and Rescue
March 23 at 9:33 PM ·

The inspiration behind this idea, actually came from neighboring and other fire departments!

We know that kids are stuck at home due to the COVID-19 outbreak. But SFD would like to make the best of it and try to brighten a young ones day!

If you have a little one that is celebrating a birthday, and who would like a little light show with some sirens, let us know! We will arrange a time to drive a fire truck or two to your house to put on the best light show we can offer! We will wish your young one a happy birthday, in a social distancing kind of way, to help lift their spirits!

If you have any questions, please contact us!
Chief Bill Halleran 641-660-6030
Captain Austin Bruns 641-541-0310
2nd Assistant Chief Jerry Smithart 641-660-5295

Stay safe!

OPEN ROAD - DRIVER EDUCATION
We are excited to announce that driver education will be available online and drive times will proceed!
All students who have enrolled in the spring Driver Ed class will receive an email with login information and payment options.
Drive times will begin this Saturday, March 29th.
We will be contacting students throughout the week to schedule drive times.
As a safety precaution, all cars have been equipped with disinfectant wipes and will be wiped down every 2 hours as groups change. The driving times will not be scheduled till a later date to wait and see guidance from Public Health and the State.
You can still enroll in the spring class by signing up at OpenRoadDriving.com
Please call 319-671-2800 with any questions. We look forward to hearing from you!
-Open Road Staff

post_text:
Students,

We are looking at holding a Tee Shirt Design contest between Sigourney Elementary/Secondary and Pekin Elementary/Secondary while we are out of school due to the Coronavirus 2020. Students from each building will submit designs to their building principals via email.

The principals will compile the designs and have teachers from their own buildings select a building winner.

The four building winners will be submitted to a panel of superintendents (not from our area or connections to our schools), which will select a winner based on the following criteria:

Coronavirus 2020
Criteria:
Fun in Nature
Positive Theme

The winning building will get a pizza party.

Designs are due to building principals by April 1. Superintendent will reveal the winner on April 7th.

Winning designs will be able to purchase this spectacular design on a shirt at a later date.

This is not intended to make light of our situation, but to get our creative minds working and to stay connected with our kids and school.

Mrs. Clarahan

Jolie Crawford
February 27 at 8:15 AM · Instagram ·

Are you ready to "Celebrate Reading" Sigourney Elementary??? Tonight is our annual Family Reading Night at Sigourney Elementary! Come join us for a fun night with activities like the Book Walk, Tattoos, PLINKO, Estimation Stations, and Scavenger Hunt. There is also a 25 cent book sale in the Commons a FREE supper, and organizations coming for the Summer Planning Fair. All PK-6th grade Sigourney Elementary students are invited to attend with an adult. Everyone student will walk away with a brand new free book of their choice and opportunities to win one of over 75 door prizes! Doors open at 5:30 and close at 7:00. Hope to see you all there!

On these days, staff will be wearing the red/white "Be Kind" tee shirts from last year. If your child no longer has their shirt or needs a new one, here is where you can order them: http://www.thethreadshop.org/store/c17/SIGOURNEY_SCHOOL_BE_KIND_SHIRTS.html . If your child does not want one of the Be Kind shirts, they can simply wear red that day instead.

We would also like to invite parents, community members, and businesses to take part in these days with us if you so choose!

post_text:
FRESHMAN DENTAL SCREENINGS

To complete the State of Iowa required dental screenings, the local I Smile Coordinator will be at our school soon. Iowa legislature passed this law that all students enrolled in 9th grade have a dental screening. The Registered Dental Hygienist will provide the screening for all students without a completed form returned to school. The dental screening is an examination of the soft and hard tissues of the mouth and will be completed with a flashlight, disposable mouth mirror and gloves.

If you do not want your child to receive this free screening from the I Smile program please contact Linda Northup, School Nurse 641 622 2350 or linda.northup@sigourneyschools.com

If you have a dentist and your child has received an exam within the past year, please contact them to fax the State of Iowa Dental Screening certificate to the school. Dental offices have this form on hand.

Fax: 641 622 3604 or 641 622 2047

post_text: Smartraining starts next week!
shared_text:
Smartraining
November 5, 2019 at 10:37 AM ·

Savage Parents: Smartraining begins next Monday November 11th. Please find your child's category and encourage them to engage in activity that will make them less susceptible to injury and stronger. This is all while being supplemented with great teamwork, mental toughness building, developing response to adversity and confidence building. This is NOT just for students in sports. We will be starting our workouts with a couple daily injury prevention exercises from Sigourney Chiropractic and Wellness 641.224.3240 Loading and lifting patterns with plyometrics (learning how to move) from our coaches and some cool down and flexibility work from Sheets Chiropractic & Wellness Inc Don't let your kid miss out! Also, if you have a JH Girl out for basketball, they will begin after Xmas break. Schedule is attached. Encourage your kid to bring a friend! Sigourney Community School District
